1️⃣ What are Generics? 🧠

Generics allow you to write type-safe, reusable code by specifying the data type at compile time.

Without Generics ❌
ArrayList list = new ArrayList();
list.add(10);
list.add("Hello"); // allowed

int x = (int) list.get(0); // casting needed

Problems:
❌ No type safety
❌ Runtime ClassCastException
❌ Manual casting

With Generics ✅
ArrayList<Integer> list = new ArrayList<Integer>();
list.add(10);
// list.add("Hello"); ❌ compile-time error

int x = list.get(0); // no casting

✔ Type safe
✔ Errors caught at compile time
✔ Cleaner code

